Considered a feminine and soft hue, many men have shied away from wearing pink. For some, pink has been a lifelong fascination, while for others it has been a shade to avoid, mock or deride for being overly feminine, frivolous and girly. Don’t be intimidated by pink, thanks to trends there are so many ways you can wear pink as a man and still be very stylish while retaining your masculinity. The outfit combination for pink is endless, from the Oxford pink shirt to the polo shirt. From the office to the club, if styled correctly can give your fashion game a level up. Pink Dress Shirts for Men
If you own a pink dress shirt, then you are a stylish man. It gives you a hint of elegance when paired with chinos, dark jeans or linen trousers. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-1103101 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Richard-Mofe-Damijo-wearing-a-pink-shirt-Photo-Ghafia-497x598.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720" /> Pink Trousers
